<headline>Severe Weather Statement issued June 21 at 10:57PM MDT until June 22 at 1:15AM MDT by NWS Pueblo</headline>
<description>...A SEVERE THUNDERSTORM WARNING REMAINS IN EFFECT UNTIL 1115 PM MDT
FOR NORTH CENTRAL CROWLEY COUNTY...
At 1057 PM MDT, a severe thunderstorm was located 12 miles southwest
of Forder, or 39 miles northwest of La Junta, and is nearly
stationary.
HAZARD...Half dollar size hail.
SOURCE...Radar indicated.
IMPACT...Damage to vehicles is expected.
This severe thunderstorm will remain over mainly rural areas of north
central Crowley County.
HAIL THREAT...RADAR INDICATED
MAX HAIL SIZE...1.25 IN
WIND THREAT...RADAR INDICATED
MAX WIND GUST...&lt;50 MPH</description>
<instruction>For your protection move to an interior room on the lowest floor of a
building.</instruction>
